# IntelliJ HTTP Client examples for technical-interview-demo
# This app does not issue JWTs and does not accept Authorization: Bearer tokens.
# Protected app requests use the configured OAuth provider login flow plus the
# technical-interview-demo-session cookie created by Spring Session.
# For 1.0, this reviewer-oriented browser session flow deliberately keeps CSRF disabled.
#
# Provider token exchange examples are for diagnostics only.
# External provider access tokens are for provider APIs, not for this app,
# and the app will not accept those tokens on /api/**.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@oauthProvider = github
#@sessionCookie = paste-technical-interview-demo-session-here
#@providerClientId = paste-provider-client-id-here
#@providerClientSecret = paste-provider-client-secret-here
#@providerAuthCode = paste-provider-auth-code-here
#@providerAccessToken = paste-provider-access-token-here

### App authentication - start the optional OAuth login flow in a browser-capable client
# This endpoint is active only when the oauth profile is enabled and the provider registration exists.
GET {{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/{{oauthProvider}}

### App authentication - verify the authenticated app session cookie
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/account
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
Accept: application/json
